SIMPLE: interchange
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interchange
<hw>In`ter*change"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Interchanged</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Interchanging</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>entrechangen</ets>, OF.
<ets>entrechangier</ets>. See <er>Inter-</er>, and
<er>Change</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To put each in the place of the other; to give and
take mutually; to exchange; to reciprocate; <as>as, to
<ex>interchange</ex> places; they <ex>interchanged</ex> friendly offices
and services.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shall <qex>interchange</qex>⟦br⟧
My waned state for Henry's regal crown.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cause to follow alternately; to intermingle; to
vary; <as>as, to <ex>interchange</ex> cares with
pleasures</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interchange</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Interchange
<hw>In`ter*change"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make an interchange;
to alternate.</def> <rj><au>Sir P. Sidney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interchange</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Interchange
<hw>In`ter*change"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>entrechange</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of mutually changing; the act of mutually
giving and receiving; exchange; <as>as, the <ex>interchange</ex> of
civilities between two persons</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Interchange</xex>
of kindnesses.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The mutual exchange of commodities between two
persons or countries; barter; commerce.</def>
<rj><au>Howell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Alternate succession; alternation; a
mingling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>interchanges</qex> of light and darkness.</q>
<rj><qau>Holder.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sweet <qex>interchange</qex>⟦br⟧
Of hill and valley, rivers, woods, and plains.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An intersection between highways, having two or more
levels and a series of connecting roadways so that traffic on one
highway may pass over or under the other highway without crossing
through the line of traffic, and vehicles may pass from one highway to
the other while traffic on both highways continues uninterrupted. A
common interchange is the <stype>cloverleaf</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interchangeability</ent>⟦br⟧
